# Board commands

Comment any of these on an issue to move it on the project board. A GitHub
Actions workflow (`board-command.yml`) parses the comment and applies the
matching mutation — no AI call in the loop, so this works whether or not the
repo has any coding agent installed.

- `/move-to-sprint N` — set the `Sprint` iteration field to sprint N.
- `/set-priority P0|P1|P2` — set the `Priority` field.
- `/complete` — set `Status` to Done.

Only users with write access to this repository can trigger these commands.
